docs.abstract: The attorney general has the power to declassify intelligence agencies’ secrets as he examines the investigation into Russia’s election interference and ties to Trump associates.
docs.snippet: The attorney general has the power to declassify intelligence agencies’ secrets as he examines the investigation into Russia’s election interference and ties to Trump associates.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has given Attorney General William P. Barr extraordinary powers to declassify intelligence secrets as part of his review into how the 2016 Trump campaign’s ties to Russia were investigated. That means Mr. Barr could make documents or information from the C.I.A. or the F.B.I. public over their intense objections, setting up a possible confrontation between the law enforcement and intelligence communities.

headline.main: Barr Got More Power to Review the Russia Inquiry. Here’s What We Know About Its Origins.
headline.print_headline: What’s Known of the Origins  Of a Russian Investigation

docs.abstract: Speaker Nancy Pelosi is using rhetorical volleys, like accusing President Trump of “a cover-up,” to ease the pressure on impeachment as she counsels a methodical strategy.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Nancy Pelosi hopped into her SUV on Wednesday for the short drive to the White House knowing full well that a presidential ambush awaited. President Trump was not “serious,” and needed a way out of negotiations over a $2 trillion infrastructure plan that he could not pay for, she told lawmakers at the Capitol an hour earlier.

headline.main: Pelosi Pushes Go-Slow Strategy on Impeachment as She Goads Trump
headline.print_headline: Pelosi Goads Trump  Even as She Eases Push for Impeachment

docs.abstract: The House Judiciary Committee voted to hold Attorney General William P. Barr in contempt after President Trump asserted executive privilege over the full Mueller report.
docs.snippet: The House Judiciary Committee voted to hold Attorney General William P. Barr in contempt after President Trump asserted executive privilege over the full Mueller report.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House Judiciary Committee voted Wednesday to recommend that the House hold Attorney General William P. Barr in contempt of Congress for failing to turn over Robert S. Mueller III’s unredacted report, hours after President Trump asserted executive privilege to shield the full report and underlying evidence from Congress.

headline.main: House Panel Approves Contempt for Barr After Trump Claims Privilege Over Full Mueller Report
headline.print_headline: House Committee Votes  To Put Barr in Contempt  In Standoff Over Report

docs.lead_paragraph: A Chinese delegation is expected to travel on Thursday to Washington to resume trade talks after negotiations had faltered.
